      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes standard benchmark cases (lid-driven cavity, Taylor-Couette) within 1% of analytical solution.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent code verification is documented in the vendor verification manual. Internal benchmark runs for Taylor-Couette flow confirm velocity profiles within 0.8% of analytical solution at equivalent Reynolds numbers. Meets MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) less than 5% for hemolysis index QoI across three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed at the nominal operating point (4.5 L/min, 3000 RPM). The fine-to-medium GCI for normalized hemolysis index was computed as 7.2%, exceeding the 5% threshold established for MRL 2. The coarse-to-medium GCI was 18.4%. The team judged the exceedance minor given that the relative hemolysis index trend was monotonically convergent and the absolute hemolysis values remained below the RH < 1 acceptance criterion across all mesh levels. The discretization error is therefore considered acceptable in the context of the overall assessment, and the decision to accept was retained without escalation of the assurance level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature) documented with measurement uncertainty within ±3% of nominal.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data report inlet flow rates measured via Coriolis flowmeter (±1.2%) and rotational speed via optical tachometer (±0.5%). Temperature controlled to 37±0.5°C. All five operating points replicated within stated uncertainty bounds. Meets MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) within 20% of experimental values across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values compared against FDA benchmark experimental data. Maximum deviation was 14.3% at the 6 L/min, 3500 RPM operating point. All five operating points within the 20% acceptance band. Meets MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (NIH, shear stress distribution, relative hemolysis index RH) directly map to clinical hemolysis risk endpoints specified in the COU.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH computed as the ratio of predicted NIH for the design variant to the predicate device NIH. This directly addresses the COU decision criterion (RH < 1). Secondary QoIs include volume-averaged scalar shear stress and exposure time, which are mechanistically linked to red blood cell damage. Meets MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
