      "rationale": "Validation was performed using the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, which shares the same impeller topology as the CPB device under assessment. Operating conditions span 3–6 L/min and 2500–3500 RPM, encompassing the COU envelope. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, matched viscosity) used in both validation experiments and COU simulations. Meets MRL 2 requirement."
